quizzes.question:
Apply the "do" and "while" keywords in their corresponding positions.
[!raw!]
var count=1;
{0} {
  document.write("hello <br />");
  count++;
}
{1} (count<=10);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The Do...While Loop[/h1]

The [b]do...while[/b] loop is a variant of the while loop. This loop will execute the code block once, [b]before [/b]checking if the condition is true, and then it will repeat the loop as long as the condition is true.

[b]Syntax:[/b] [code format="js" ][b]do [/b]{
   code block
}
[b]while [/b](condition);[/code]
[note]Note the [b]semicolon [/b]used at the end of the do...while loop.[/note]
[b]Example:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="672"]var i=20;
[b]do [/b]{  
  document.write(i + "<br />");
  i++;  
}
[b]while [/b](i<=25); [/code]
This prints out numbers from 20 to 25. [img id="2757" width="100%"]
[note]The loop will always be executed [b]at least once[/b], even if the condition is false, because the code block is executed before the condition is tested.[/note]
